vec accessoire","value":"2,37","displayDimension":"2,37 m","unit":"m","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":3,"note":""},{"type":"Largeur avec accessoire","value":"1,62","displayDimension":"1,62 m","unit":"m","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":4,"note":""},{"type":"Profondeur avec accessoire","value":"15,5","displayDimension":"15,5 cm","unit":"cm","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":5,"note":""}],"shape":"","materialsAndTechniques":"huile sur toile","placeOfCreation":"","dateOfDiscovery":"","placeOfDiscovery":"","provenance":"","historicalContext":[],"objectHistory":"Selon toute vraisemblance, l\u0027inventaire de l\u0027h\u00e9ritage de Maerten Daey, Amsterdam, le 3 novembre 1659 (dans la pi\u00e8ce donnant sur la rue : \u0022deux portraits de Marten Soolemans, et Ooppie Coppit); apparemment, Oopjen Coppit, veuve de Maerten Soolmans, apporta les portraits lors de son second mariage avec Maerten Day; bien qu\u0027apr\u00e8s la mort d\u0027Oopjen, en 1689, ils ne figurent pas dans l\u0027h\u00e9ritage de Jan Soolmans (mort en 1691), fils issu du second mariage, la famille Daey a d\u00fb \u00e0 un certains moment entrer en possession de ces deux portraits ; selon John Smith (1836), R. Priuscenaar (R.M. Priuscenaar ?) et Adriaan Daey ach\u00e8terent les portraits de Hendrik Daey en 1798 \u00e0 Alkmaar pour 4 000 florins; en 1799 ils furent vendus pour 12 000 florins au marchand et collectionneur Pieter van Winter (1745-1807) ; son gendre, Jonkheer Willem van Loon (1794-1847); la veuve de ce dernier Anna Louisa Agatha, en h\u00e9rita apr\u00e8s la mort de son \u00e9poux Willem van Loon; apr\u00e8s sa mort, les tableaux furent vendus au baron Gustave de Rothschild (1829-1911); l\u0027acquisition des deux portraits a \u00e9t\u00e9 faite par l\u2019\u00c9tat fran\u00e7ais et l\u2019\u00c9tat n\u00e9erlandais : la France a acquis le portrait de Oopjen Coppit, gr\u00e2ce au m\u00e9c\u00e9nat exceptionnel de la Banque de France.","jabachInventory":"","napoleonInventory":"","previousOwner":[],"acquisitionDetails":[{"mode":"achat par l\u0027\u00c9tat","doubt":"","dates":[{"type":"date","value":"21\/10\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date","value":"24\/11\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date de comit\u00e9\/commission","value":"02\/12\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date","value":"09\/12\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date","value":"11\/12\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date","value":"15\/12\/2015","startYear":2015,"endYear":2015},{"type":"date de l\u0027arr\u00eat\u00e9\/d\u00e9cision","value":"25\/01\/2016","startYear":2016,"endYear":2016},{"type":"date de comit\u00e9\/commission","value":"03\/02\/2016","startYear":2016,"endYear":2016},{"type":"date de l\u0027inscription sur l\u0027inventaire","value":"09\/03\/2016","startYear":2016,"endYear":2016}]}],"ownedBy":"Etat","heldBy":"Mus\u00e9e du Louvre, D\u00e9partement des Peintures","longTermLoanTo":"","index":{"Mode d\u0027acquisition":[{"value":"achat par l\u0027\u00c9tat"}]},"bibliography":[{"bibliographyRef":"Havard, Henry, \u00ab A propos de deux tableaux de Rembrandt \u00bb, Gazette des Beaux-Arts, f\u00e9vrier 1879, p.147-151","bibliographyDate":"f\u00e9vrier 1879","bibliographyDetail":"p. 147-151","comparison":false},{"bibliographyRef":"Bikker, Jonathan, Portraits de Marten Soolmans et Oopjen Coppit, Paris, Louvre \u00e9ditions \/ Somogy, (Collection Solo), 2017","bibliographyDate":"2017","bibliographyDetail":"","comparison":false},{"bibliographyRef":"Schatborn, Peter ; Starcky, Emmanuel ; Curie, Pierre (dir.), Rembrandt intime, cat. exp. (Paris, Mus\u00e9e Jacquemart-Andr\u00e9, du 16 septembre 2016 au 23 janvier 2017), Bruxelles, Fonds Mercator, 2016","bibliographyDate":"2016","bibliographyDetail":"p. 43","comparison":false},{"bibliographyRef":"Bruyn, Josua (dir.), A Corpus of Rembrandt Paintings t.II : 1631-1634, La Haye, Martinus Nijhoff, 1986